hh3cDot11QoS.name: hh3cDot11QoS

revisions.description: The initial revision of this MIB module.

hh3cDot11QoS.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China Http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cDot11QoS.description: This MIB provides information about WLAN QoS configuration. GLOSSARY IEEE 802.11 Standard to encourage interoperability among wireless networking equipment. WMM WMM is a wireless QoS protocol designed to preferentially transmit packets with high priority, thus guaranteeing better QoS services for voice and video applications in a wireless network. EDCA Enhanced distributed channel access (EDCA) is a channel contention mechanism designed by WMM to preferentially transmit packets with high priority and allocate more bandwidth to such packets. AC Access category (AC), is used for channel contention. WMM defines four access categories; they are AC-VO (voice), AC-VI (video), AC-BE (best-effort), and AC-BK (background) in the descending order of priority. When contending for a channel, a high-priority AC preempts a low-priority AC. CAC Connection admission control (CAC) limits the number of clients that are using high-priority ACs (AC-VO and AC-VI) to guarantee sufficient bandwidth for existing high-priority traffic. U-APSD Unscheduled automatic power-save delivery (U-APSD) is a new power saving mechanism defined by WMM to enhance the power saving capability of clients. SVP SpectraLink voice priority (SVP) is a voice priority protocol designed by the Spectralink company to guarantee QoS for voice traffic.

Hh3cDot11WMMSVPMapAC.name: Hh3cDot11WMMSVPMapAC
Hh3cDot11WMMSVPMapAC.description: The AC level which SVP packets are assigned to. acbk : for background access category, acbe : for best-effort access category, acvi : for voice access category, acvo : for video access category, disable : for disable SVP feature

Hh3cDot11WMMCACPolicy.name: Hh3cDot11WMMCACPolicy
Hh3cDot11WMMCACPolicy.description: The policy of CAC. channelUtilization : the channel utilization-based admission policy for CAC, userNumber : the users-based admission policy for CAC

hh3cDot11RadioWmmCfgTable.name: hh3cDot11RadioWmmCfgTable
hh3cDot11RadioWmmCfgTable.description: The table defines the basic parameters for WMM configuration.

hh3cDot11RadioWmmCfgEntry.name: hh3cDot11RadioWmmCfgEntry
hh3cDot11RadioWmmCfgEntry.description: This entry contains the basic information for WMM configuration.

hh3cDot11RadioWmmEnabled.name: hh3cDot11RadioWmmEnabled
hh3cDot11RadioWmmEnabled.description: Represents the status of WMM in radio. 'true' : The WMM function is enabled. 'false': The WMM function is disabled.

hh3cDot11RadioSVPMapToAC.name: hh3cDot11RadioSVPMapToAC
hh3cDot11RadioSVPMapToAC.description: Represents the AC level which SVP packets are assigned to. 'acbk' : Specifies the AC-BK (background traffic) queue. 'acbe' : Specifies the AC-BE (best-effort traffic) queue. 'acvi' : Specifies the AC-VI (video traffic) queue. 'acvo' : Specifies the AC-VO (voice traffic) queue. 'disable' : Disable SVP packet mapping.

hh3cDot11RadioCacPolicy.name: hh3cDot11RadioCacPolicy
hh3cDot11RadioCacPolicy.description: Represents the policy for CAC. CAC requires that a client obtain permission of the AP before it can use a high-priority AC for transmission, thus guaranteeing bandwidth to the clients that have gained access. CAC controls real time traffic (AC-VO and AC-VI traffic) but not common data traffic (AC-BE and AC-BK traffic).

hh3cDot11RadioCacChlUtlValue.name: hh3cDot11RadioCacChlUtlValue
hh3cDot11RadioCacChlUtlValue.description: Represents Maximum channel utilization rate, that is, the medium time of the accepted AC-VO traffic and AC-VI traffic to the valid time during the unit time. This object can be set only if the value of hh3cDot11RadioCacPolicy is ChannelUtilization.

hh3cDot11RadioCacUserNum.name: hh3cDot11RadioCacUserNum
hh3cDot11RadioCacUserNum.description: Represents the users-based admission policy for CAC. This object can be set only if the value of hh3cDot11RadioCacPolicy is userNumber.

hh3cDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfgTable.name: hh3cDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfgTable
hh3cDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfgTable.description: The table defines the basic parameters for EDCA configuration of radio.

hh3cDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfgEntry.name: hh3cDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfgEntry
hh3cDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfgEntry.description: This entry contains the basic information for EDCA configuration of radio.

hh3cDot11RadioWmmAC.name: hh3cDot11RadioWmmAC
hh3cDot11RadioWmmAC.description: Represents the AC level index of EDCA parameters of radio. 'acbk' : Specifies AC-BK (background traffic). 'acbe' : Specifies AC-BE (best-effort traffic). 'acvi' : Specifies AC-VI (video traffic). 'acvo' : Specifies AC-VO (voice traffic).

hh3cDot11RadioWmmAifsn.name: hh3cDot11RadioWmmAifsn
hh3cDot11RadioWmmAifsn.description: Represents AIFSN parameter of EDCA. The value range of this object is limited by the radio chip capability.

hh3cDot11RadioWmmEcwMin.name: hh3cDot11RadioWmmEcwMin
hh3cDot11RadioWmmEcwMin.description: Represents ECWmin parameter of EDCA. The value range of this object is limited by the radio chip capability. ECWmin parameter of EDCA must be smaller than ECWmax parameter.

hh3cDot11RadioWmmEcwMax.name: hh3cDot11RadioWmmEcwMax
hh3cDot11RadioWmmEcwMax.description: Represents ECWmax parameter of EDCA. The value range of this object is limited by the radio chip capability. ECWmin parameter of EDCA must be larger than ECWmax parameter.

hh3cDot11RadioWmmTxoplimit.name: hh3cDot11RadioWmmTxoplimit
hh3cDot11RadioWmmTxoplimit.description: Represents TXOPLimit parameter of EDCA, the value must be in the range of 0 to 65535 (in units of 32 microseconds). The TXOP value of 0 indicates that only one MPDU can be transmitted. The range of this argument is limited by the radio chip capability.

hh3cDot11RadioWmmNoAck.name: hh3cDot11RadioWmmNoAck
hh3cDot11RadioWmmNoAck.description: Represents the AC to adopt the No ACK policy. The protocol defines two ACK policies: Normal ACK and No ACK.

hh3cDot11StationWmmEdcaTable.name: hh3cDot11StationWmmEdcaTable
hh3cDot11StationWmmEdcaTable.description: The table defines the basic parameters for EDCA configuration of station.

hh3cDot11StationWmmEdcaEntry.name: hh3cDot11StationWmmEdcaEntry
hh3cDot11StationWmmEdcaEntry.description: This entry contains the basic information for EDCA configuration of client. If CAC is enabled for an AC, CAC is also enabled for ACs with higher priority. For example, if CAC is enabled for AC-VI, CAC is also enabled for AC-VO. However, enabling CAC for AC-VO does not enable CAC for AC-VI.

hh3cDot11StationWmmAC.name: hh3cDot11StationWmmAC
hh3cDot11StationWmmAC.description: Represents the AC level index of EDCA parameters of client. 'acbk' : Specifies AC-BK (background traffic). 'acbe' : Specifies AC-BE (best-effort traffic). 'acvi' : Specifies AC-VI (video traffic). 'acvo' : Specifies AC-VO (voice traffic).

hh3cDot11StationWmmTxoplimit.name: hh3cDot11StationWmmTxoplimit
hh3cDot11StationWmmTxoplimit.description: Represents TXOPLimit parameter of EDCA, the value is in units of 32 microseconds. The TXOP value of 0 indicates that only one MPDU can be transmitted.

hh3cDot11StationWmmCacEnabled.name: hh3cDot11StationWmmCacEnabled
hh3cDot11StationWmmCacEnabled.description: Represents the AC to adopt the No ACK policy. The protocol defines two ACK policies: Normal ACK and No ACK. Only if the value of hh3cDot11StationWmmAC is 'acvo' or 'acvi', Cac can be set correctly here.

hh3cDot11WmmResetRadioByAP.name: hh3cDot11WmmResetRadioByAP
hh3cDot11WmmResetRadioByAP.description: Clear the WMM statistics information of the radio of the specified AP or all radios. The meaning of this object is the same as hh3cDot11APElementIndex, it represents the index of AP element. If the value of this object is set to 0xFFFFFFFF, WMM statistics information of all radios will be cleared. The value of this object is always 0 with the get operation.

hh3cDot11WmmResetStationByAP.name: hh3cDot11WmmResetStationByAP
hh3cDot11WmmResetStationByAP.description: Clear the WMM statistics information of the clients associated with the specified AP, or of all clients. The meaning of this object is the same as hh3cDot11APElementIndex, it represents the index of AP element. If set with the 0xFFFFFFFF, it will clear the WMM statistics information of all clients. The value of this object is always 0 with the get operation.

hh3cDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfg2Table.name: hh3cDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfg2Table
hh3cDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfg2Table.description: The table defines the basic parameters for EDCA configuration of radio.

hh3cDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfg2Entry.name: hh3cDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfg2Entry
hh3cDot11RadioWmmEdcaCfg2Entry.description: This entry contains the basic information for EDCA configuration of radio.

hh3cDot11RdWmmAC.name: hh3cDot11RdWmmAC
hh3cDot11RdWmmAC.description: Represents the AC level index of EDCA parameters of radio. 'acbk' : Specifies AC-BK (background traffic). 'acbe' : Specifies AC-BE (best-effort traffic). 'acvi' : Specifies AC-VI (video traffic). 'acvo' : Specifies AC-VO (voice traffic).

hh3cDot11RdWmmAifsn.name: hh3cDot11RdWmmAifsn
hh3cDot11RdWmmAifsn.description: Represents AIFSN parameter of EDCA. The value range of this object is limited by the radio chip capability.

hh3cDot11RdWmmEcwMin.name: hh3cDot11RdWmmEcwMin
hh3cDot11RdWmmEcwMin.description: Represents ECWmin parameter of EDCA. The value range of this object is limited by the radio chip capability. ECWmin parameter of EDCA must be smaller than ECWmax parameter.

hh3cDot11RdWmmEcwMax.name: hh3cDot11RdWmmEcwMax
hh3cDot11RdWmmEcwMax.description: Represents ECWmax parameter of EDCA. The value range of this object is limited by the radio chip capability. ECWmin parameter of EDCA must be larger than ECWmax parameter.

hh3cDot11RdWmmTxoplimit.name: hh3cDot11RdWmmTxoplimit
hh3cDot11RdWmmTxoplimit.description: Represents TXOPLimit parameter of EDCA, the value must be in the range of 0 to 65535 (in units of 32 microseconds). The TXOP value of 0 indicates that only one MPDU can be transmitted. The range of this argument is limited by the radio chip capability.
